reviewText:
Hiya ! Here comes the poulpy review of The Deadly Tower of Monsters":

// What made me want to try this game ? //
> The art style and the prospect to live through a full-length 50's science fiction B-movie. And the ability to play different characters. I was very intrigued by that robot.

// Is there anything about this game that you did not know before playing it but now you DO enjoy ? //
> Yes: the ability to come back to different areas of the tower and the weapons leveling. And the comments from the Director (love this).

// Is there anything about this game that you did not know before playing it but now you DON'T enjoy ? //
> Yes: movement controls can be cluncky at times.

// Have you finished the game at the time of this review ? //
> No. But I like this game well enough to try and finish it.

// To whom would you recommend this game ? //
> To anyone who is a fan of 50's SF lore and who is not bothered by the top down view."
